{
  "text": "We modeled the data following the framework described by [CITATION_1] for analyzing conjoint measurement experiments (see also chapter 8, [CITATION_2] . They define three nested models that can be fit to describe the choices of the observers in order of complexity: an independence model, an additive model, and a saturated model. We begin the description with the additive model and then describe the simpler and more complex models with respect to it.",
